text_run.content: In this reference, you can find descriptions of monitoring metrics for Zilliz Cloud clusters, as well as alert items that you can set up at organization and project levels.

The total amount of persistent storage consumed by data and indexes.
The count of search and query requests per second. VPS is not available for query requests because query operations does not involve vectors.
Search QPS is indicated by the blue line.

The time elapsed between a client sending a read request (search and query request) to a server and the client receiving a response. It includes an average latency and a P99 latency.
Search latency is indicated by the blue line.

The time elapsed between a client sending a write request (insert and upsert request) to a server and the client receiving a response. It includes an average latency and a P99 latency.
Insert latency is indicated by the blue line.
Upsert latency is indicated by the green line.
Delete latency is indicated by the orange line.
The percentage of timeout read requests in all requests per second.
The percentage of timeout write requests in all requests per second.
The count of collections created in a cluster.
The count of entities created in a cluster.
The count of entities loaded (actively served) by a cluster.

Project alerts focus on the operational aspects of your clusters, including notifications on the CU usage, QPS thresholds, latency issues, and request anomalies, ensuring you maintain optimal cluster performance.
Zilliz Cloud provides predefined default alert targets to ensure that critical issues are quickly identified and addressed with the appropriate actions.
: Triggered at >70% utilized computational power for 10+ minutes.
: Triggered at >90% utilized computational power for 10+ minutes.
: Triggered at >70% utilized CU capacity for 10+ minutes.
: Triggered at >90% utilized CU capacity for 10+ minutes.
Triggered at >50 search operations per second for 10+ minutes.
Triggered at P99 latency >1,000ms for 10+ minutes.
Triggered at P99 latency >1,000ms for 10+ minutes.
In addition to the predefined default project alerts , you can also configure custom alert targets as needed.
